      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I would not recommend taking a double dose of propranolol without consulting a doctor. While it may provide temporary relief, excessive use can lead to serious side effects, such as dizziness, fainting, and increased heart rate. I strongly advise against self-medicating, especially with a medication meant for anxiety, and instead, consider reaching out to a healthcare professional for a proper evaluation. They can help determine the underlying cause of your symptoms and provide a safe and effective treatment plan.",
